1
00:00:12,429 --> 00:00:14,681
[soft clicking]

2
00:00:27,277 --> 00:00:29,738
[CROWD cheering]

3
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:32,199
[HOMURA] Everybody feeling
good out there?

4
00:00:32,241 --> 00:00:34,826
So much love!
You guys are amazing!

5
00:00:34,868 --> 00:00:37,621
We hope you're having
the time of your lives tonight.

6
00:00:37,663 --> 00:00:40,165
'Cause we're gonna keep singing
our hearts out for you!

7
00:00:40,207 --> 00:00:43,168
Are you ready for the next one?

8
00:00:43,210 --> 00:00:46,797
Here we go!

9
00:00:46,838 --> 00:00:49,216
♪

10
00:00:53,345 --> 00:00:55,847
[YUKI]
Those unending ordinary days.

11
00:00:57,724 --> 00:01:00,644
The existence
known as life itself.

12
00:01:03,188 --> 00:01:04,731
‐[AKIRA] Miss Yuki!
‐[YUKI gasps]

13
00:01:04,773 --> 00:01:06,525
[people screaming]

14
00:01:06,567 --> 00:01:08,610
[YUKI]
If suddenly, one day,

15
00:01:08,652 --> 00:01:12,489
without any warning,
it were all to disappear...

16
00:01:13,824 --> 00:01:15,617
[YUA]
Everyone, run!

17
00:01:15,659 --> 00:01:18,704
[screaming continues]

18
00:01:18,745 --> 00:01:20,956
[YUKI]
The spirit of those people,

19
00:01:20,998 --> 00:01:24,376
their unique memories
and experiences...

20
00:01:24,418 --> 00:01:27,754
Miss Yuki!

21
00:01:27,796 --> 00:01:29,464
Akira!

22
00:01:31,091 --> 00:01:33,093
[YUKI]
Where would they all end up?

23
00:01:34,928 --> 00:01:35,846
Yuki.

24
00:01:36,972 --> 00:01:38,056
Souma.

25
00:01:38,098 --> 00:01:40,267
[explosion]

26
00:01:56,700 --> 00:02:00,162
‐[door opens]
‐[alarm blaring]

27
00:02:00,203 --> 00:02:02,164
[footsteps approaching]

28
00:02:06,668 --> 00:02:08,045
[BLACK COAT A]
Get up.

29
00:02:09,421 --> 00:02:10,547
[YUKI whimpers softly]

30
00:02:10,589 --> 00:02:12,299
Hurry up, there's no time to‐‐

31
00:02:12,341 --> 00:02:14,051
‐[choking]
‐[BLACK COAT B yells]

32
00:02:14,092 --> 00:02:16,011
‐[BLACK COAT B yells]
‐[BLACK COAT A screams]

33
00:02:16,053 --> 00:02:18,263
[panting]

34
00:02:18,305 --> 00:02:19,598
[YUKI shudders]

35
00:02:20,849 --> 00:02:22,059
Come on.

36
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,769
[alarm blaring continues]

37
00:02:29,941 --> 00:02:31,360
[inhales sharply]

38
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:34,154
Well, shit.

39
00:02:34,196 --> 00:02:35,989
[TAKUYA grunting]

40
00:02:39,868 --> 00:02:42,412
‐[explosion]
‐[glass shattering]

41
00:02:44,831 --> 00:02:46,249
[YUKI gasps]

42
00:02:49,419 --> 00:02:50,712
[TAKUYA grunts]

43
00:04:30,937 --> 00:04:33,356
Look, I'm just
the courier, okay?

44
00:04:33,398 --> 00:04:36,818
As soon as I can deliver you,
my contract ends.

45
00:04:36,860 --> 00:04:39,863
Just keep quiet
till then, got it?

46
00:04:41,323 --> 00:04:42,783
‐[helicopter blades whirring]
‐[YUKI gasps]

47
00:04:45,786 --> 00:04:46,995
[BOTH gasp]

48
00:04:47,037 --> 00:04:48,747
Are you kidding me?

49
00:04:48,789 --> 00:04:50,749
♪

50
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:53,752
[TAKUYA sighs]

51
00:04:57,088 --> 00:04:58,340
Guess we're doing this.

52
00:04:59,883 --> 00:05:01,593
[gasps, whimpers]

53
00:05:02,886 --> 00:05:03,970
[gasps]

54
00:05:06,139 --> 00:05:08,266
♪

55
00:05:19,736 --> 00:05:21,029
[grunts]

56
00:05:23,573 --> 00:05:26,034
[tires screeching]

57
00:05:26,076 --> 00:05:27,369
[TAKUYA grunting]

58
00:05:31,706 --> 00:05:33,708
[grunting]

59
00:05:37,254 --> 00:05:38,171
[YUKI gasps]

60
00:05:40,924 --> 00:05:42,384
[YUKI whimpers]

61
00:05:42,425 --> 00:05:44,469
[energy humming]

62
00:05:46,638 --> 00:05:47,514
Huh?

63
00:05:48,557 --> 00:05:50,308
[MONK grunts]

64
00:05:51,935 --> 00:05:54,437
[groaning]

65
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:58,775
[tires screeching]

66
00:06:00,735 --> 00:06:02,237
[CITIZEN #1]
Stupid bastard!

67
00:06:02,279 --> 00:06:03,655
What the hell are you doing?!

68
00:06:03,697 --> 00:06:05,031
‐[CITIZEN #2] That was crazy!
‐[panting]

69
00:06:05,073 --> 00:06:06,491
The hell?

70
00:06:06,533 --> 00:06:08,034
[horns honking]

71
00:06:08,076 --> 00:06:10,745
‐You okay?
‐[YUKI panting]

72
00:06:10,787 --> 00:06:12,831
[honking continues]

73
00:06:17,752 --> 00:06:19,045
♪

74
00:06:27,137 --> 00:06:28,722
[indistinct yelling]

75
00:06:36,229 --> 00:06:37,272
Come on. Shit.

76
00:06:37,314 --> 00:06:39,357
♪

77
00:06:45,822 --> 00:06:47,198
‐[gasps]
‐[grunts]

78
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,491
Come on!

79
00:06:49,659 --> 00:06:50,785
Hurry!

80
00:06:54,748 --> 00:06:55,999
[TAKUYA grunts]

81
00:07:02,297 --> 00:07:03,798
‐[beeping]
‐[inhales sharply]

82
00:07:06,301 --> 00:07:07,928
How?

83
00:07:07,969 --> 00:07:10,430
[BLACK COAT on radio] Find them!
They should still be nearby.

84
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:16,519
[beeping]

85
00:07:16,561 --> 00:07:18,313
[steady beep]

86
00:07:18,355 --> 00:07:20,649
[EIJI] She's within
normal values for now.

87
00:07:20,690 --> 00:07:23,234
Hey, man, who the hell
were those guys?

88
00:07:23,276 --> 00:07:25,820
I was aware
the Agency was dangerous,

89
00:07:25,862 --> 00:07:28,573
but no one told me something
like that would happen.

90
00:07:28,615 --> 00:07:30,075
[EIJI]
Check her brain waves.

91
00:07:31,368 --> 00:07:33,787
She's still in
a state of confusion.

92
00:07:33,828 --> 00:07:35,622
We should really
let her rest now.

93
00:07:35,664 --> 00:07:36,748
[EIJI]
No need.

94
00:07:36,790 --> 00:07:37,999
Besides, I've got to figure out

95
00:07:38,041 --> 00:07:39,626
what was done to her
at that facility.

96
00:07:39,668 --> 00:07:41,628
Yeah, that's
a real good question.

97
00:07:41,670 --> 00:07:43,838
What do you know?

98
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:46,841
♪

99
00:07:57,644 --> 00:07:59,646
[keyboard keys clacking]

100
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:05,360
[EIJI]
The Tama‐shi.

101
00:08:05,402 --> 00:08:06,486
[TAKUYA]
Hmm?

102
00:08:06,528 --> 00:08:09,030
‐And what is that?
‐[YUKI gasps]

103
00:08:09,072 --> 00:08:11,866
[EIJI] It seems they are
the victims of the Lost.

104
00:08:11,908 --> 00:08:13,493
Three years ago.

105
00:08:13,535 --> 00:08:15,662
[TAKUYA scoffs]
So, what are you saying?

106
00:08:15,704 --> 00:08:17,998
I was attacked
by some kinda ghost?

107
00:08:18,039 --> 00:08:22,252
No. To begin with, no one's
ever found the victims' bodies.

108
00:08:22,293 --> 00:08:23,920
We've only ever
called them Tama‐shi

109
00:08:23,962 --> 00:08:25,338
for the sake of convenience.

110
00:08:25,380 --> 00:08:26,423
[gasps]

111
00:08:26,464 --> 00:08:27,716
[EIJI]
That girl?

112
00:08:27,757 --> 00:08:29,884
Is the only
known survivor of Lost.

113
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:32,470
That's why she's important.

114
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:33,388
[gasps]

115
00:08:34,973 --> 00:08:36,683
[EIJI]
She's a valuable sample.

116
00:08:38,393 --> 00:08:40,353
One we're lucky to get back.

117
00:08:40,395 --> 00:08:43,189
Your bedside manner
needs some work.

118
00:08:47,193 --> 00:08:49,863
Yuki, we met before.

119
00:08:49,904 --> 00:08:51,072
Do you remember?

120
00:08:53,491 --> 00:08:56,244
[EIJI] Probably not,
she was pretty young.

121
00:09:02,459 --> 00:09:03,710
Fascinating stuff.

122
00:09:03,752 --> 00:09:05,670
Either way, my job here's done.

123
00:09:05,712 --> 00:09:08,840
I don't want to get
caught up in anything.

124
00:09:08,882 --> 00:09:11,092
Don't forget
to transfer the funds over.

125
00:09:12,218 --> 00:09:13,553
[EIJI]
Wait.

126
00:09:13,595 --> 00:09:16,473
I know you just got back
and the timing sucks.

127
00:09:16,514 --> 00:09:19,225
But there's another job
for you if you want it.

128
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:20,351
[TAKUYA]
Huh?

129
00:09:21,853 --> 00:09:25,356
[EIJI] I need you to go
to the missing city, Lost.

130
00:09:25,398 --> 00:09:28,109
[TAKUYA scoffs]
Are you kidding?

131
00:09:28,151 --> 00:09:31,613
That whole area's been
quarantined by the government.

132
00:09:31,654 --> 00:09:34,074
[EIJI] Yes. They've been
secretly investigating it

133
00:09:34,115 --> 00:09:35,658
since the disaster.

134
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:39,329
But there's been no progress
for the past three years.

135
00:09:39,370 --> 00:09:42,207
No human has ever returned
from that spot alive.

136
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:46,878
But robots can't be used
for the investigations.

137
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:49,923
Rumor is, all forms of
communication within the area

138
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:51,216
have been completely blocked.

139
00:09:52,509 --> 00:09:54,594
Correct me if I'm wrong,
but I thought that place

140
00:09:54,636 --> 00:09:57,013
was just a big void
of nothingness now.

141
00:09:57,055 --> 00:09:59,099
[KIKYO]
That's not quite accurate.

142
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:02,018
The state of nothingness
exists there.

143
00:10:02,060 --> 00:10:03,478
[TAKUYA]
How's that different?

144
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:05,146
Here, take a look at this.

145
00:10:05,188 --> 00:10:08,483
It's a message.
In quantum encryption.

146
00:10:13,154 --> 00:10:14,906
[TAKUYA]
"Yuki, I'm waiting at Lost."

147
00:10:14,948 --> 00:10:15,907
[YUKI gasps]

148
00:10:15,949 --> 00:10:17,659
What the hell is that?

149
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:19,911
[EIJI]
This is from Yuki's father.

150
00:10:19,953 --> 00:10:21,287
[YUKI inhales sharply]

151
00:10:21,329 --> 00:10:23,540
My father's alive?

152
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:26,876
Are you sure?

153
00:10:33,967 --> 00:10:36,177
[EIJI]
We haven't confirmed it yet.

154
00:10:36,219 --> 00:10:38,388
As you know, three years ago,

155
00:10:38,429 --> 00:10:41,516
he tried to stop the occurrence
of Lost and got caught up in it.

156
00:10:42,976 --> 00:10:45,145
And now,
seemingly out of the blue,

157
00:10:45,186 --> 00:10:46,437
we get this message.

158
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:49,065
[YUKI sobbing]

159
00:10:49,107 --> 00:10:50,400
[EIJI] Either way,

160
00:10:50,441 --> 00:10:52,485
going to Lost should
bring you some answers.

161
00:10:56,614 --> 00:10:59,868
Huh? So, the job, is it her?

162
00:10:59,909 --> 00:11:02,370
Yes, that's right.

163
00:11:02,412 --> 00:11:04,956
I want you to deliver
Yuki to Lost.

164
00:11:04,998 --> 00:11:06,082
[TAKUYA sighs]

165
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:08,877
[EIJI]
Sorry, Takuya.

166
00:11:08,918 --> 00:11:10,712
You're the only one I can ask.

167
00:11:17,719 --> 00:11:20,138
[TAKUYA] You'd better make it
worth my while.

168
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:21,264
[YUKI]
Hmm?

169
00:11:23,766 --> 00:11:25,476
[EIJI]
Don't worry, it will be.

170
00:11:27,395 --> 00:11:29,439
♪

171
00:11:35,778 --> 00:11:38,907
[pop music playing]

172
00:11:38,948 --> 00:11:41,951
[MAN humming along]

173
00:11:47,999 --> 00:11:49,667
Wonder where I should
hold the RL meeting

174
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:52,337
since it'll just be me
again this year.

175
00:11:52,378 --> 00:11:53,379
[chuckles]

176
00:11:53,421 --> 00:11:54,672
‐[vehicle approaching]
‐Hmm?

177
00:11:54,714 --> 00:11:56,216
‐[screams]
‐[tires screeching]

178
00:11:58,051 --> 00:12:00,595
‐Geek, what's up?
‐[GEEK] Takuya!

179
00:12:00,637 --> 00:12:03,014
Jeez. You almost gave me
a freakin' heart attack!

180
00:12:03,056 --> 00:12:05,516
[TAKUYA] You're beautiful when
you're angry, you know that?

181
00:12:05,558 --> 00:12:06,768
[GEEK]
Would you shut up?

182
00:12:06,809 --> 00:12:08,770
Can you look at her for me?

183
00:12:08,811 --> 00:12:10,063
[GEEK]
Yeah, no prob.

184
00:12:10,104 --> 00:12:11,522
Hmm?

185
00:12:15,276 --> 00:12:18,196
Are you kidding me?
What's with the girl?

186
00:12:18,238 --> 00:12:20,657
Have you seriously resorted
to kidnapping?

187
00:12:20,698 --> 00:12:22,283
[TAKUYA]
Well, something like that.

188
00:12:24,369 --> 00:12:27,288
[GEEK] I should have her
fixed up in about 30 minutes.

189
00:12:27,330 --> 00:12:29,207
There's some food over there
if you're hungry.

190
00:12:31,084 --> 00:12:32,919
[TAKUYA]
Thanks, I'll pass.

191
00:12:34,003 --> 00:12:38,383
[GEEK] So, where are you off to
with that cutie in tow, anyway?

192
00:12:38,424 --> 00:12:40,093
Is it a date?

193
00:12:40,134 --> 00:12:41,636
I'm so jealous I could puke.

194
00:12:41,678 --> 00:12:44,180
Ugh, long story.

195
00:12:44,222 --> 00:12:46,349
The short of it is,
I'm headin' to Lost.

196
00:12:46,391 --> 00:12:47,684
‐[GEEK gasps]
‐[tool clangs]

197
00:12:50,603 --> 00:12:52,355
[GEEK whispering]
Are you nuts?

198
00:12:52,397 --> 00:12:55,608
Come outside.
We need to talk in private.

199
00:12:55,650 --> 00:12:58,111
Dude, that's insane.

200
00:12:58,152 --> 00:13:00,321
You're really serious?

201
00:13:00,363 --> 00:13:02,115
She's the lone survivor of Lost?

202
00:13:02,156 --> 00:13:04,409
It sounds crazy, but, yeah.

203
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:07,453
Listen, man, I know
you've never been the type

204
00:13:07,495 --> 00:13:10,373
to get blinded
by a big paycheck or anything,

205
00:13:10,415 --> 00:13:11,958
so I don't know
why you're doing this,

206
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,209
but it's too dangerous.

207
00:13:13,251 --> 00:13:16,296
Besides, you're already
injured as it is.

208
00:13:16,337 --> 00:13:18,006
[TAKUYA]
Just part of the job.

209
00:13:18,047 --> 00:13:19,716
[GEEK]
I get it, but this is...

210
00:13:19,757 --> 00:13:22,010
[TAKUYA] I follow through
on my contracts.

211
00:13:22,051 --> 00:13:24,721
Sort of a personal policy.

212
00:13:24,762 --> 00:13:26,264
No matter what they might be,

213
00:13:26,306 --> 00:13:28,558
my packages get delivered.

214
00:13:28,599 --> 00:13:30,727
[GEEK]
I know. I respect that.

215
00:13:30,768 --> 00:13:32,687
But "personal policies"
be damned,

216
00:13:32,729 --> 00:13:34,105
you're walking
into your own grave.

217
00:13:34,147 --> 00:13:35,398
Tell me why!

218
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:37,233
Why would you go
that far for some girl?

219
00:13:37,275 --> 00:13:39,444
She's a stranger, right?

220
00:13:41,112 --> 00:13:43,156
Look, stranger or not,

221
00:13:43,197 --> 00:13:45,074
she's just a package.

222
00:13:47,327 --> 00:13:48,995
[footsteps receding]

223
00:13:49,037 --> 00:13:50,038
[BOTH gasp]

224
00:13:54,751 --> 00:13:55,960
Damn it.

225
00:13:59,839 --> 00:14:02,342
♪

226
00:14:09,807 --> 00:14:12,602
[YUKI]
Oh, Father. Souma.

227
00:14:16,898 --> 00:14:18,983
Akira.

228
00:14:19,025 --> 00:14:20,693
It's been three years.

229
00:14:20,735 --> 00:14:22,403
Tonight, demonstrations
are being held

230
00:14:22,445 --> 00:14:23,988
to honor the victims of Lost.

231
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:25,531
We head there now.

232
00:14:26,866 --> 00:14:28,451
[PROTESTER]
The government should announce

233
00:14:28,493 --> 00:14:30,370
the truth to the public!

234
00:14:30,411 --> 00:14:32,497
[PROTESTERS]
Tell the public the truth!

235
00:14:35,041 --> 00:14:36,292
[WOMAN]
I can see it.

236
00:14:38,628 --> 00:14:40,963
The alignment of your stars.

237
00:14:41,005 --> 00:14:44,592
The fate that you bear upon
your shoulders is a heavy one.

238
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:55,019
[cell phone ringing]

239
00:14:56,312 --> 00:14:58,940
Takuya, looks like
the Agency's expanded

240
00:14:58,981 --> 00:15:00,358
their search to this area.

241
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:03,236
We're on the move now,
just to be safe.

242
00:15:03,277 --> 00:15:06,364
Find a route to Lost and head
that way as soon as possible.

243
00:15:06,406 --> 00:15:08,658
Well, yeah, I'd love to do that.

244
00:15:08,699 --> 00:15:09,992
But now the girl is gone.

245
00:15:10,034 --> 00:15:10,910
[BOTH gasp]

246
00:15:12,161 --> 00:15:13,621
[EIJI]
What?!

247
00:15:13,663 --> 00:15:16,416
‐[keys clacking]
‐[rapid beeping]

248
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:19,710
[GEEK] Crap, where the heck
did she go?!

249
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:21,838
What did I do? Did I say
something I shouldn't have?

250
00:15:21,879 --> 00:15:23,798
[TAKUYA] An acquaintance of mine
is looking for her.

251
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:26,092
I'll head to Lost
as soon as she's found.

252
00:15:26,134 --> 00:15:29,345
[water spritzing]

253
00:15:29,387 --> 00:15:31,889
[cell phone ringing]

254
00:15:35,351 --> 00:15:36,310
Hmm.

255
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:41,232
Hey.

256
00:15:41,274 --> 00:15:44,193
[YUMIKO]
It's been a long time, Takuya.

257
00:15:44,235 --> 00:15:45,611
[TAKUYA]
Yeah, sorry, but I was hoping

258
00:15:45,653 --> 00:15:47,405
you'd check
something out for me.

259
00:15:47,447 --> 00:15:48,990
Oh, yeah, what's that?

260
00:15:49,031 --> 00:15:52,160
I need you to tell me
the best way to get into Lost.

261
00:15:52,201 --> 00:15:54,412
[YUMIKO]
What? Why are you going there?

262
00:15:54,454 --> 00:15:55,580
What in the world are you even‐‐

263
00:15:55,621 --> 00:15:57,206
Please, Yumiko.

264
00:16:00,001 --> 00:16:01,127
[sighs]

265
00:16:01,169 --> 00:16:02,420
[YUMIKO]
Of course.

266
00:16:02,462 --> 00:16:04,839
I know I have data
from a previous search.

267
00:16:04,881 --> 00:16:06,299
I'll send it over.

268
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:09,051
[TAKUYA]
Thanks. I owe you one.

269
00:16:09,093 --> 00:16:10,136
[beeps]

270
00:16:10,178 --> 00:16:11,888
That jerk.

271
00:16:11,929 --> 00:16:13,848
He really hasn't changed at all.

272
00:16:17,477 --> 00:16:20,354
♪

273
00:16:26,235 --> 00:16:28,696
It's a dangerous path you're on.

274
00:16:28,738 --> 00:16:30,740
You should turn back.

275
00:16:30,781 --> 00:16:32,283
If not...

276
00:16:35,244 --> 00:16:37,205
I can't turn back, though.

277
00:16:37,246 --> 00:16:38,539
Nowhere to go.

278
00:16:42,835 --> 00:16:45,546
Did you really think
you could do this on your own?

279
00:16:46,506 --> 00:16:48,007
Get on.

280
00:16:48,049 --> 00:16:49,675
Come on, hurry up.

281
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:55,223
You're going, right?
You're gonna go find your dad?

282
00:16:59,101 --> 00:17:01,938
Look, you don't have
to believe in me, okay?

283
00:17:01,979 --> 00:17:04,732
But you saw your dad's message.

284
00:17:06,150 --> 00:17:08,486
At the very least,
believe in him.

285
00:17:10,780 --> 00:17:11,864
[YUKI inhales sharply]

286
00:17:13,950 --> 00:17:15,409
Hmm!

287
00:17:15,451 --> 00:17:16,744
[engine idling]

288
00:17:36,722 --> 00:17:38,182
‐[helicopter blades whirring]
‐[YUKI gasps]

289
00:17:38,224 --> 00:17:39,517
Well, well.

290
00:17:39,559 --> 00:17:41,852
Looks like they consider
you pretty valuable.

291
00:17:43,229 --> 00:17:44,605
[grunts]

292
00:17:47,024 --> 00:17:48,818
‐It's fine.
‐[YUKI] Huh?

293
00:17:48,859 --> 00:17:50,152
We can just lose 'em again.

294
00:17:50,194 --> 00:17:51,237
[gunfire]

295
00:17:52,363 --> 00:17:53,990
[YUKI screaming]

296
00:17:55,575 --> 00:17:56,951
You kidding me?

297
00:18:08,713 --> 00:18:10,464
[yells]

298
00:18:22,184 --> 00:18:23,269
[grunts]

299
00:18:24,729 --> 00:18:25,563
[PILOT screams]

300
00:18:25,605 --> 00:18:26,480
[explosion]

301
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:29,066
[YUKI screaming]

302
00:18:29,108 --> 00:18:30,443
[TAKUYA grunts, sighs]

303
00:18:31,444 --> 00:18:33,362
[YUKI gasping]

304
00:18:34,739 --> 00:18:36,324
[TAKUYA]
Shit!

305
00:18:36,365 --> 00:18:38,075
[grunting]

306
00:18:39,994 --> 00:18:40,870
[YUKI gasps]

307
00:18:44,165 --> 00:18:45,708
[YUKI]
Enough!

308
00:18:45,750 --> 00:18:47,209
Don't do this.

309
00:18:47,251 --> 00:18:49,211
It has nothing to do with you.

310
00:18:50,171 --> 00:18:52,173
Even if I do get to Lost...

311
00:18:52,214 --> 00:18:55,176
♪

312
00:18:55,217 --> 00:18:57,094
...everybody is dead, anyway.

313
00:18:57,136 --> 00:18:58,512
Even my father!

314
00:18:58,554 --> 00:19:00,181
[TAKUYA]
Don't give up.

315
00:19:00,222 --> 00:19:02,975
Did you see it
with your own eyes?

316
00:19:03,017 --> 00:19:05,603
You won't know for sure
till you go.

317
00:19:07,521 --> 00:19:09,398
[YUKI]
But it all disappeared.

318
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:10,858
Everything!

319
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:13,194
[TAKUYA]
Go back. Be sure.

320
00:19:15,071 --> 00:19:17,531
[YUKI] At this rate,
we'll never make it.

321
00:19:17,573 --> 00:19:18,741
[TAKUYA groans]

322
00:19:19,909 --> 00:19:21,786
♪

323
00:19:23,621 --> 00:19:25,706
‐[energy humming]
‐[energy blasting]

324
00:19:25,748 --> 00:19:27,333
[tires screeching]

325
00:19:27,375 --> 00:19:29,919
♪

326
00:19:31,087 --> 00:19:33,047
Akira?!

327
00:19:33,089 --> 00:19:34,215
[gunfire]

328
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:38,302
[gasps]
Did you call him here somehow?

329
00:19:45,601 --> 00:19:46,936
[grunts]

330
00:19:48,229 --> 00:19:51,023
‐[AKIRA groaning]
‐[YUKI screaming]

331
00:19:51,065 --> 00:19:51,982
Yuki!

332
00:19:54,652 --> 00:19:55,945
[YUKI grunts]

333
00:19:56,987 --> 00:19:57,947
[AKIRA grunts]

334
00:19:59,782 --> 00:20:01,075
[rapid gunfire]

335
00:20:02,243 --> 00:20:03,619
[MONK groaning]

336
00:20:06,163 --> 00:20:07,790
[explosion]

337
00:20:11,877 --> 00:20:14,004
♪

338
00:20:21,762 --> 00:20:23,639
We should be out
of their range now.

339
00:20:25,975 --> 00:20:27,101
[TAKUYA grunts]

340
00:20:27,143 --> 00:20:29,061
[energy hums]

341
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:32,022
[car door opens]

342
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:33,023
[car door closes]

343
00:20:33,065 --> 00:20:34,483
Sorry.

344
00:20:34,525 --> 00:20:36,193
Didn't mean
to cause any trouble.

345
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:38,612
Just make sure
you collect her properly.

346
00:20:40,114 --> 00:20:42,700
Once you've done that,
you can kill the guy.

347
00:20:42,742 --> 00:20:44,493
[SUZUNA]
Will do.

348
00:20:44,535 --> 00:20:46,579
‐[SOUMA] By the way...
‐[SUZUNA] Hmm?

349
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:48,581
[SOUMA]
Tell me, Suzuna,

350
00:20:48,622 --> 00:20:51,083
why didn't you
report the situation sooner?

351
00:20:54,128 --> 00:20:56,547
What, did you think
you could get ahead of me?

352
00:20:57,840 --> 00:21:00,926
♪

353
00:21:07,183 --> 00:21:10,561
[KIKYO] I wonder, was this
the best course of action?

354
00:21:10,603 --> 00:21:13,147
What are you implying, huh?

355
00:21:13,189 --> 00:21:14,982
[KIKYO]
Come on.

356
00:21:15,024 --> 00:21:18,110
You know very well how dangerous
it is to approach Lost.

357
00:21:18,152 --> 00:21:21,071
For starters, the fact that
nobody's ever reached it,

358
00:21:21,113 --> 00:21:22,615
that's a lot.

359
00:21:22,656 --> 00:21:24,325
[EIJI]
Well, at the very least,

360
00:21:24,366 --> 00:21:27,203
we can rest assure
that the Agency won't kill her.

361
00:21:27,244 --> 00:21:30,456
Not as long as she still
holds some value to them.

362
00:21:30,498 --> 00:21:32,166
[KIKYO]
But what about him?

363
00:21:32,208 --> 00:21:34,835
[EIJI] Either way it goes,
he'll be a useful sample.

364
00:21:36,420 --> 00:21:39,215
Beyond that,
the Observer will decide.

365
00:21:39,256 --> 00:21:42,009
♪

366
00:21:57,900 --> 00:22:00,361
He's down, but still breathing.

367
00:22:00,402 --> 00:22:02,488
I can do this myself.

368
00:22:09,119 --> 00:22:10,371
[gunshot]

369
00:23:43,881 --> 00:23:46,300
♪

370
00:23:50,679 --> 00:23:53,349
[YUKI]
Next episode, "Sacrifice."

